<h1 class='center'>Executing R Scripts in Rails</h1>

<div class="description col-md-6 col-md-offset-3">
  Below are a few demonstrations of how to run R scripts within a Rails app.  The results are graphed and exported as a PNG file that can easily be displayed.
</div>

<div class="col-md-12">
  <div class="scripts">
    <div class="col-md-offset-3">
      <ul class="script_link">
        <li>
          <%= link_to 'Chick Weights', r_script_path(script: 'Chick Weights') %>
          - Basic barplot, no color
        </li>
        <li>
          <%= link_to 'Random Barplot', r_script_path(script: 'Random Barplot') %>
          - using 'Blues' from RColorBrewer
        </li>
        <li>
          <%= link_to 'Overlayed Histogram', r_script_path(script: 'Overlayed Histogram') %>
          - Swiss Education dataset and 'Pastel2' from RColorBrewer
        </li>
        <li>
          <%= link_to 'Color Styles', r_script_path(script: 'Color Styles') %>
          - Color Palettes provided by RColorBrewer package
        </li>
      </ul> 
    </div>
  </div>
</div>